						               													<description>Set of miniatures wargame rules for fighting battles of the American Civil War circa 1862.  From the cover:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;quot;Being a set of very playable recreational Wargame rules that will create, to some degree, the excitement and pageantry of Tactical Battles of the late War for Southern Independence&amp;quot;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Assuming 25mm\28mm figures are used:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game scale: One inch = 22 yards&amp;#10;One infantry figure = 25 men&amp;#10;Twenty infantry figures equal a 500 men regiment&amp;#10;Six figures and three gun models equal a 6-gun battery&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Reduced scale rulers are provided for playing with figures smaller than 25mm\28mm.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Mounted cavalry is not covered in the rules (it's assumed that they have dismounted prior to the start of the game).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Sequence of play:&amp;#10;1) Movement Phase: Brigades are moved in order of a draw from a deck of cards. Command rolls are made to determine which regiments in the brigade may move. A number of dice are then rolled to determine how far the regiments may move.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;2) Firing Phase 1 - All stationary artillery fires and morale tests from casualties are resolved.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;3) Firing Phase 2 - All stationary infantry fires and morale tests from casualties are resolved.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;4) Firing Phase 3 - All &amp;quot;move and fire&amp;quot; artillery fires and morale tests from casualties are resolved.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;5) Firing Phase 4 - All moving infantry fires and morale tests from casualties are resolved.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;6) Combat Morale Phase - Test morale for charging and charged units.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;7) Close Combat Phase - Fight all close combats and test morale.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;8) Morale Adjustment Phase - Make all permanent morale adjustments due to various conditions.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;9) Rally Phase - Attempt to rally all Routed units from the previous game turn.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;10) Major Morale Phase - Determine each army's Major Morale state and act accordingly.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Order of Battle for Antietam is given at the end of the rules.  No scenarios are included.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
